<TEXT>
<P>
It took me the entire length of the opening credits for the CBS series, "The 
People Next Door," to realize that this is garbage destined for the sitcom 
trash can. A half-hour later I was convinced, thanks to the idiotic concept, 
the pathetic script and the infuriating canned laughter at every ridiculous 
line and facial expression. My disbelief at how this rubbish gets on the air is 
only surpassed by my amazement that actual salaries are distributed to the 
so-called writers. Naturally I won't be giving this one a second chance and to 
prevent future abominations, I suggest we all do the same. Until we do, the 
only people laughing will continue to be the writers trotting off to cash their 
checks at the bank. 
</P>
<P>
Francis Albert, Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA100889-0005 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 117554 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 8, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
