<SECTION>
<P>
TV Times; Page 2; Television Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
122 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<TEXT>
<P>
That "Married . . . With Children" failed to receive a single Emmy nomination 
(let alone award) is a disgrace! Are the academy voters hypocrites, or are they 
just so infused with self-importance that they can't find it in their hearts to 
enjoy and acknowledge mere entertainment? Because that's all "MWC" is -- no 
messages, no social relevance, just vulgar, tasteless low comedy. But brilliant 
low comedy! Fall-on-your-face-from-laughing low comedy! Can't they see that? 
</P>
<P>
Speaking on behalf of the unwashed masses without reputations to protect, I'd 
like to present everyone connected with "MWC" an honorary award for giving us 
the funniest American situation comedy since "I Love Lucy" went into reruns. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Jones, Sun Valley 
</P>
</TEXT>
