<P>
PEJORATIVE ROOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
While Karl Schoenberger, reviewing Ahn Junghyo's "White Badge," states that the 
word gook had its origin during the Korean War (Book Review, Sept. 10), this 
expression actually was commonly used by GIs throughout the Pacific during 
World War II. 
</P>
<P>
B. W. MARTINEZ 
</P>
<P>
SAN BERNARDINO 
</P>
