<P>
CHECK OUT B-52S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After reading Steve Hochman's review (Record Rack, Sept. 24) of the Sugarcubes 
latest album, may I suggest he listen to the B-52s for the "mischievous" 
quality he seeks? 
</P>
<P>
It still amazes me that no one has heard this obvious rip-off of a sound 
created right here in the U.S.A. Good music doesn't have to come from an 
exotic-sounding place like: Reykjavik to be "brand-spanking new." 
</P>
<P>
PAM TATE 
