<HEADLINE>
<P>
ABOUT THAT WORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Would someone care to explain to the foreigners east of California Movieland's 
eternal love affair with the F-word? We who have grown tired and bored with "F" 
wonder why Hollywood is still so titillated by "F." 
</P>
<P>
Recently, I overheard a man who was renting a movie video ask the clerk what 
the "F" rating was. He claimed he found "F" annoying and that it destroyed his 
enjoyment of a movie when he had to continually wade mentally though the "F's" 
to catch the rest of the dialogue. 
</P>
<P>
Add a rating . . . G, PG, PG-13, R, X, and "F" (thank you very much). Join the 
real world and get bored with "F." 
</P>
<P>
RON and VERA MARTINOFF 
</P>
<P>
Kerville, Tex. 
</P>
</TEXT>
