<HEADLINE>
<P>
PERCEPTIONS OF COLOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We tell ourselves about the problem, examples are given and we show the 
results. But no one seems to proffer a solution or even a suggestion of one. 
Are we hopelessly and inexorably bound toward a nation divided by race? If that 
is the only answer then what was experienced 25 years ago will be nothing 
compared to the violence ahead. 
</P>
<P>
The question of race will never be totally eradicated. That's a constant. 
However, we can ill afford to ignore the alternatives. We must instruct our 
children and we must not quit in our effort to solve this dilemma. 
</P>
<P>
RODNEY K. BOSWELL, Los Angeles 
</P>
