<DATE>
<P>
October 8, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Travel; Part 7; Page 3; Column 1; Travel Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
1239 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
JERRY HULSE'S TRAVEL TIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jerry Hulse 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Here is a new twist for travelers planning a visit along Northern California's 
Mendocino Coast. Vacation homes are up for grabs between Navarro Ridge to the 
south and Ten Mile River to the north. Scores of choices. Convenient to 
Mendocino Village, redwood forest, the dramatic Pacific shoreline. Rates 
$70/$250 a night to $425/$950 a week. Other rentals by the month. Ocean views, 
rivers, creeks, woods. Fully furnished rentals. Some with fireplaces. 
</P>
<P>
Contact Mendocino Coast Reservations, P.O. Box 1143, Mendocino, Calif. 95460. 
Telephone (707) 937-5033. For sightseeing information, write to the Ft. 
Bragg/Mendocino Coast Chamber of Commerce, P.O. Box 1141, Ft. Bragg 95437, or 
call (707) 964-3153. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Swiss Holiday 
</P>
<P>
With the inauguration by Swissair of direct service between Los Angeles and 
Switzerland in mid-December, A.J.S. Travel Consultants will be packaging 
ski-week vacations to nearly a dozen Swiss resorts. A choice of 17 first-class 
and deluxe hotels at Zermatt, Grindelwald, St. Moritz, Klosters, Arosa, 
Crans-Montana, Davos, Engelberg, Interlaken, Wilderswil. Prices: $363/$1,180, 
plus air fare. Includes accommodations, breakfast/dinner daily, service 
charges, taxes. Swissair will be checking passenger baggage direct from LAX to 
the ski resorts. Weekly departures through mid-April. 
</P>
<P>
For details on A.J.S. ski packages, contact travel agents or A.J.S. Travel 
Consultants, 177 Beach 116th St., Rockaway Park, N.Y. 11694. Call A.J.S. 
toll-free at (800) 221-5002. A.J.S. also will arrange for stopovers in Geneva 
or Zurich and will issue Swiss rail passes. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call Swissair toll-free at (800) 221-4750, or the Swiss 
National Tourist Office in San Francisco at (415) 362-2260. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
More on Home Exchanges 
</P>
<P>
World Home Exchange Network of San Francisco is providing a new computerized 
service for its members. Exchanges available on short notice. No directories, 
no fuss. The company operates two programs. One involves a 
straight-across-the-board swap. The other is a host program whereby homeowners 
welcome other homeowners. Example: You host a Parisian for a week in your home 
and later the Parisian hosts you in Paris. Opportunities worldwide. Memberships 
include unlimited exchange requests, plus a quarterly newsletter explaining 
methods for arranging a swap. Write for a brochure to World Home Exchange 
Network, 878 30th St., San Francisco 94121, or call toll-free (800) SAY-WHEN. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Hawaii 
</P>
<P>
Veteran travel authority Ricci Zuckerman has turned to specializing in Hawaii. 
Books retail packages, airline tickets, hotels, car rentals. Serves both 
budget/upscale travelers. Assists with anything involving the islands. 
Weddings, hiking, scuba diving, biking, fishing, luaus. 
</P>
<P>
Contact Zuckerman c/o To Hawaii Only, 15634 Brookhurst St., Westminster 92638, 
or telephone toll-free (800) 222-4852. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another Hawaii specialist is providing free nights at 32 
hotels/condominiums. You pay for the first day and get a free night later. 
Price categories vary. Choices of properties on all the islands. Contact 
Classic Hawaii c/o The Bary Group, Pier 26, The Embarcadero, San Francisco 
94105, or call (415) 495-5022. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Backroads Bicycling 
</P>
<P>
A series of six-day bike tours through Baja California by Backroads Bicycle 
Touring of Berkeley is being planned for December/January. The program includes 
a clockwise loop along the Sea of Cortez to Cabo San Lucas, with a northern 
return along the Pacific to La Paz. Bikers will pedal through El Triunfo, San 
Bartolo, Buena Vista, plus other small villages. In Cabo San Lucas they'll be 
headquartered at Hotel Finesterra. Other nights will be spent in posadas. An 
average of 40 miles per day on the road. Rates from $894 (meals, 
accommodations, safety helmet, guides, support vehicles for hauling luggage, 
etc.). 
</P>
<P>
For a 52-page catalogue describing the Baja trip and other bike tours, contact 
Backroads Bicycle Touring, 1516 5th St., Berkeley 94710-1713, or call (415) 
527-1555 or toll-free (800) 533-2573 (outside California). 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Jamaica 
</P>
<P>
In a play for the tourist, a Jamaica hotel is offering to pay one free air fare 
for two guests traveling together for a minimum of seven nights. Offer is good 
through Dec. 14. The hotel is the 236-room Jamaica. Provides all-inclusive 
adult vacations. A 27-acre property with golf, snorkeling, scuba diving, 
sailing, catamaran cruises, bicycling, windsurfing. This is a packaged deal 
that includes room, meals, open bar, airport transfers. No tipping. 
</P>
<P>
Contact International Lifestyles toll-free at (800) 858-8009. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Letter From Kathleen 
</P>
<P>
"I've just returned from a holiday in Italy, and I want to share a treasure -- 
Hotel Tramonto D'Oro in Praiano on the Amalfi Coast between Positano and 
Amalfi. An incredible bargain. Rooms for about $45 U.S. including breakfast. 
Full pension available for slightly more (about $20). The hotel is family-run 
and the staff is professional and wonderful! A huge swimming pool. The view is 
spectacular as the hotel overlooks the sea. Other rooms nearby are three times 
the price. Praiano is a great place to rest and relax. A small, quiet town. For 
those who want more excitement, there are plenty of nearby places. I'm planning 
a return trip." 
</P>
<P>
Having been to Praiano, I agree with Kathleen Nizro. A real bargain hotel along 
one of the world's romantic coastlines. Hotel Tramonto D'Oro: 40 rooms with 
bath, telephone, private balcony. Open year-round. See your travel agent or 
write to Hotel Tramonto D'Oro, via Gennaro Capriqline 119, 84010 Praiano, 
Costiera Amalfiana, Italy. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Skiers 
</P>
<P>
For skiers on a budget, try Sunrise Resort Lodge in eastern Arizona. An early 
season rate (Nov. 17 to Dec. 16) for only $170 for two guests for two nights. 
Includes lift tickets as well as lodging. (Prices will be hiked to $270 during 
the holiday season.) Sunrise is operated by the Apache Indians. A lift capacity 
of 1,300 skiers per hour. Terrain is second only to Taos. A choice of three 
mountains and more than 60 trails. Night skiing on weekends. Two new quad chair 
lifts will double Sunrise peak's capacity this season. Ski school instruction 
is offered for all ages. A shuttle bus delivers skiers to the lifts. 
</P>
<P>
Write to Sunrise, P.O. Box 217, McNary, Ariz. 85930. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Reader Recommendations 
</P>
<P>
Colorado -- Pat Longville, Long Beach: The Talbott House, 932 Colorado Ave., 
Glenwood Springs, Colo. 81601. Cherry Talbott, proprietor. Rates: $27 single, 
$42 double. 
</P>
<P>
England -- Aileen and Howard Routledge, Palm Desert: "Holly Lodge, Upper 
Oldfield Park, Bath. Run by Carolle Sellick. Has just been awarded a 
commendation by the British Tourist Authority as the 'Best B&amp;B in the 
West.' Views over Bath are magnificent. Decor is outstanding. Cost: $82 U.S. 
per couple per night, including a full English breakfast." 
</P>
<P>
Scotland -- Mr. and Mrs. M. J. Martini, Orange: St. Margaret's Bed &amp; 
Breakfast, Mallig, Scotland. "A dream of a B&amp;B in the home of Mrs. Carmine 
Macdonald, featuring a splendid view of the sea to the isles of Skye, Rhum and 
Eigg. Doubles, 10.50 per person. Singles, 11.50." 
</P>
<P>
New Zealand -- Whitey Stanforth, Westminster: "People travel the world over to 
golf and I'm one of them. I would like to make some of the others aware of the 
friendliest, least crowded and most beautiful place I've ever visited to play 
golf. I speak of New Zealand. My trip was organized by Paul Walker, New Zealand 
Golf Excursions, 2041 Rosecrans Ave., No. 103, El Segundo 90245." 
</P>
