<TEXT>
<P>
With ticket sales in excess of $100 million, a sequel to Disney's "Honey, I 
Shrunk the Kids" is a foregone conclusion. Not so definite: the direction in 
which it'll be headed. 
</P>
<P>
To cover its bases, Disney's registered these titles with the MPAA: "Honey, I 
Can't Get the Kids Out of My Head," "Honey, I Turned the Kids Into Animals," 
"Honey, I Turned the Kids Into Giants," "Honey, I Faxed the Kids," "Honey, I 
Turned the Kids Invisible," "Honey, I Sent the Kids to the Moon," "Honey, I 
Xeroxed the Kids" and "Honey, I Ate the Kids." 
</P>
