<P>
SLAIN WOMAN FOUND IN BURNING APARTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The body of a 39-year-old woman was found Saturday by firefighters responding 
to reports of a blaze in her Van Nuys apartment. 
</P>
<P>
The shooting victim, Carol Ann Hix, was found shortly after 3 p.m. in a complex 
in the 15800 block of Vanowen Street, Los Angeles Police Detective Paul Stewart 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Police are seeking Nancy Crue, 42, of Van Nuys, in connection with the slaying, 
Stewart said. The cause of death appeared to be a gunshot wound from a small 
caliber weapon. 
</P>
<P>
The fire, which police said appeared to have been arson, was reported by a 
resident of the apartment building. Damage was slight and limited to one room, 
Stewart said. 
