BLAZES CAUSES $250,000 DAMAGE TO TIRE STORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire raced through a Van Nuys tire store Saturday night, collapsing the roof 
and causing an estimated $250,000 damage, the Los Angeles City Fire Department 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
About 90 firefighters from 18 companies put out the blaze at the Auto Master 
Tire store, 14212 Oxnard St., in about 40 minutes, Fire Department spokesman 
Greg Acevedo said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out shortly after 7 p.m. The cause is under investigation. 
</P>
