<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC 10 ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
GOAL-LINE FUMBLE SAVES CAL, 26-21 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A goal-line fumble by San Jose State tailback Sheldon Canley in the fourth 
quarter preserved California's 26-21 victory Saturday in a nonconference game 
at Berkeley. 
</P>
<P>
The Spartans had driven to Cal's one-yard-line on a fourth-quarter drive given 
renewed life in a fourth-down situation when punter Jim Hughes faked the kick 
and threw a 31-yard first-down pass. 
</P>
<P>
But with San Jose State poised to take the lead, Cal linebacker David Ortega 
stripped the ball from Canley as he was crossing into the end zone and 
cornerback Doug Parrish recovered the fumble. 
</P>
<P>
The victory margin came courtesy of a 50-yard Robbie Keen field goal and a 
safety -- Cal's first in more than three years. 
</P>
<P>
The safety was a result of three consecutive sacks in the waning minutes of the 
third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Linebacker Danny Slevin sacked San Jose State's Matt Veatch for a loss of nine 
yards, pushing the Spartans back to their 10-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
On the next play, linebacker Cornell Collier got Veatch for six more yards, and 
on the play in which Cal got the safety, it was Collier again, catching Veatch 
in the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
The Bears are 2-3. San Jose State, which beat Stanford a week earlier, is 2-2. 
</P>
<P>
The Cal defense gave up 406 yards of total offense. But the Spartans lost three 
fumbles and had five penalties, including an offensive pass interference call 
that negated a 48-yard play in the game's final minute and ended San Jose 
State's final threat. 
</P>
<P>
Fresno State 35, Oregon State 18 -- Sophomore quarterback Mark Barsotti ran for 
two touchdowns and passed for another to lead the undefeated Bulldogs of the 
Big West Conference past the Beavers at Fresno. 
</P>
<P>
Barsotti scored on a one-yard run in the first quarter and then completed an 
88-yard touchdown pass to Dwight Pickens early in the second quarter as Fresno 
pulled ahead, 21-0. 
</P>
<P>
Fresno (5-0) scored again on a two-yard run by Myron Jones. 
</P>
<P>
Oregon State (2-3) cut the margin to 21-6 at halftime on field goals of 43 and 
21 yards by Troy Bussanich. 
</P>
<P>
Pat Chaffey's one-yard scoring run early in the third quarter got Oregon State 
within nine points, but Fresno State sealed the victory with a pair of 
time-consuming drives. 
</P>
<P>
Jones scored on a one-yard run to cap off a 75-yard drive, and Barsotti had a 
one-yard touchdown run to finish an 84-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
"The two main possessions we had in the second half were awesome drives," 
Fresno State Coach Jim Sweeney said. 
</P>
<P>
Fresno State has won 12 consecutive games since a 21-10 loss to Oregon State 
last year at Corvallis. 
</P>
<P>
Matt Booher had to replace Oregon State starting quarter Nick Schichtle, who 
bruised his shoulder on the Beavers' second offensive play. Booher had 85 yards 
rushing and 136 passing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
