<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
FANN'S LATE TOUCHDOWN HELPS CS NORTHRIDGE TO WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Albert Fann scored on a four-yard run with 1:43 left as Cal State Northridge 
rallied for a 34-33 victory over Cal Lutheran Saturday night at Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge tried for a two-point conversion, but quarterback Sherdrick Bonner 
was sacked by the Kingsmen's Mike Mollinado. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran had taken a 33-28 lead when Mike Sylvester intercepted a pass by 
Bonner and returned it 33 yards for a touchdown. The Kingsmen counted on 
touchdown runs of 66, 20 and 41 yards by Craig Ashley. Ashley finished with 151 
yards in 11 carries. 
</P>
<P>
Fann, who scored on an 11-yard run in the third quarter to give Northridge a 
21-18 lead, finished with 99 yards in 25 carries. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge improved to 4-2. Cal Lutheran dropped to 1-4. 
</P>
<P>
La Verne 23, Whittier 19 -- Mark Brown threw touchdown passes of 62 and 36 
yards to Anthony Grove in the fourth quarter to give the Leopards the win at La 
Verne. 
</P>
<P>
Brown completed 14 of 37 passes for 240 yards and three touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
Gaylan Sweet rushed for 108 yards in 30 carries and two touchdowns for 
Whittier. 
</P>
<P>
Claremont-Mudd 42, Trinity University 20 -- Quarterback Mike Pembroke threw 
four touchdown passes and ran for another to lead the Stags to a win at San 
Antonio. 
</P>
<P>
Pembroke completed eight of 14 passes for 184 yards. His favorite target was 
Darin Carlsen, who had three catches for 77 yards, including touchdown 
receptions of 37 and nine yards. 
</P>
<P>
Pembroke also ran for 48 yards in six carries, including a nine-yard touchdown 
run that gave the Stags a 42-6 lead in the third quarter. Trinity scored two 
touchdowns in the fourth quarter to close out the scoring. 
</P>
<P>
Claremont-Mudd improved to 1-3. Trinity dropped to 0-4. 
</P>
<P>
UC Santa Barbara 24, Sonoma St. 3 -- Quarterback Steve Armstrong passed for two 
touchdowns and fullback Chuy Ornales rushed for 131 yards and a touchdown to 
lead the Gauchos to a win at Rohnert Park. 
</P>
<P>
UC Santa Barbara (3-2) took a 14-0 lead in the first quarter when Armstrong 
threw a 27-yard touchdown pass to Brian Fleming and a nine-yard score to Khaleb 
Shahbo. 
</P>
<P>
Ed Beaulac's 39-yard field goal cut Sonoma State's deficit to 14-3 in the 
second quarter, but Ornales scored on a one-yard run in the second quarter to 
put the Gauchos ahead, 21-3. Todd Reynolds kicked a 21-yard field goal in the 
third quarter to finish the scoring. 
</P>
<P>
U. San Diego 31, Pomona-Pitzer 6 -- Senior running back Todd Jackson ran for 
116 yards and two touchdowns in the first half to lead the Toreros to a win 
over the Sagehens at San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson finished with 117 yards in 17 carries. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego improved to 5-0, the first time since 1981 that the Toreros have 
opened with five consecutive wins. 
</P>
<P>
Portland St. 55, Cal Poly SLO 26 -- Rinaldo Shackelford caught three touchdown 
passes and ran for another to lead the Vikings to victory at San Luis Obispo. 
</P>
<P>
Shackelford caught seven passes for 215 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Quarterback Keith Jarrett completed 20 of 36 passes for 357 yards and three 
touchdowns for San Luis Obispo (2-3). 
</P>
