FLORIDA DEFEATS LOUISIANA STATE ON LAST-SECOND, 41-YARD FIELD GOAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BATON ROUGE, La. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Florida kicker Arden Czyzewski, making his first varsity appearance, kicked a 
41-yard field goal as time expired Saturday night to give Florida a 16-13 
victory over Louisiana State. 
</P>
<P>
Czyzewski replaced senior letterman John David Francis in the Gator lineup 
after Francis had kicked one field goal and missed another. 
</P>
<P>
Florida Coach Galen Hall said: "I just decided to go with Arden and see what he 
could do." 
</P>
<P>
LSU's David Browndyke tied the score with a 36-yard field goal with 1:19 to 
play. 
</P>
<P>
Huey Richardson had four sacks, Richard Fain had two interceptions and Emmitt 
Smith rushed for 126 yards and a touchdown to lead Florida (4-1 and 2-1). LSU 
is 1-3 and 0-1. 
</P>
