<TEXT>
<P>
Big Earl, runner-up to Sunday Silence in the Super Derby at Bossier, La., on 
Sept. 24, tested positive to more than the legal amount of phenylbutazone and 
probably will be disqualified, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
State racing steward C.L. Webb said a blood test after the race showed 9.3 
milligrams of phenylbutazone -- nearly twice the legal limit. 
</P>
<P>
Disqualification would cost owner-trainer Jerry Cart his $200,000 share of the 
$1-million purse. 
