<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE YEAMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Southern California Christian 18, Village Christian 14 -- Josh Carlson scored 
on runs of three and two yards as Southern California Christian (3-2) rallied 
for a nonleague win at Kennedy High. 
</P>
<P>
Carlson scored the winning touchdown with 2:42 remaining on a two-yard run that 
capped a 15-play, 70-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
Village Christian took the lead, 14-10, with 1:42 remaining in the third 
quarter after an 11-yard touchdown burst by tailback Chad Everett (111 yards in 
17 carries). 
</P>
<P>
Rick Nichols scored from three yards with 9:17 left in the first half to give 
Village Christian (3-2) a 7-0 lead. MIKE YEAMAN 
</P>
