<HEADLINE>
<P>
MANY CLOSURES TO MARK COLUMBUS DAY MONDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Monday is Columbus Day, commemorating the day Christopher Columbus discovered 
America in 1492. All state and federal offices and courthouses will be closed 
in observance of the holiday. 
</P>
<P>
In observance of the holiday: 
</P>
<P>
BANKS: Banks and savings and loan institutions will be closed. 
</P>
<P>
MAIL: Post offices will be closed and mail deposited in mailboxes will be 
picked up according to the posted holiday schedule. 
</P>
<P>
COUNTY: The County Clerk's office will be closed. All other county offices will 
be open and operating. 
</P>
<P>
CITIES: All 28 city halls will remain open, and regularly scheduled council 
meetings will be held. 
</P>
<P>
SCHOOLS: All schools, including colleges and universities, will remain open. 
City and county libraries will be open. 
</P>
<P>
TRASH: There will be regular trash pickup by city and county refuse workers. 
</P>
<P>
TRANSPORTATION: Orange County Transit District buses will run on their regular 
schedules. 
</P>
<P>
PARKING: Metered parking will be enforced throughout the county. 
</P>
<P>
City- and county-operated park and recreation facilities will be open regular 
hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
