<HEADLINE>
<P>
UCI EDGES NO. 1 CAL IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UC Irvine, the nation's second-ranked water polo team, defeated No. 1 
California, 13-12, in six overtimes Saturday when senior Julian Harvey broke 
free from his defender and scored from six meters out. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine improved its record to 11-2. Cal is now 13-2. 
</P>
<P>
Harvey scored with two minutes 16 seconds remaining in the sixth three-minute 
overtime period. The score was tied, 10-10, after regulation play and tied at 
12 after two overtime periods. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine stopped California's 13-game winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
California tied the game in regulation on Julian Bailey's man-up goal with just 
one second left in regulation play. 
</P>
