<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STUART MATTHEWS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Valley Christian 26, Orange Lutheran 6 -- Orange Lutheran was held scoreless 
until 28 seconds remained. 
</P>
<P>
With time running out, Orange Lutheran quarterback Lenny Gavin threw a pass 
intended for junior wide receiver Phil Matheson. Valley Christian defensive 
back Todd Harrison tipped the ball, but Matheson came away with it en route to 
a 62-yard touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
It was the first touchdown Valley Christian has yielded in three weeks, said 
Coach Mike Wunderly. 
</P>
<P>
Valley Christian opened the scoring at the start of the second quarter on a 
one-yard run by Mark Kortenhoeven. The senior running back carried the ball 20 
times for 130 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Quarterback Chris Miller ran five yards for the second touchdown with 46 
seconds left in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Miller then connected with senior Sam Sybesma on a nine-yard touchdown pass 
with 8:55 left in the game. 
</P>
<P>
The loss dropped Orange Lutheran's record to 2-3 overall, 0-2 in the Olympic 
League. Valley Christian is now 5-0. 
</P>
<P>
Estancia 21, Orange 0 -- Estancia High School's defense posted its fourth 
shutout in five games at Fred Kelly Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Estancia tailback Josh Wojtkiewicz gained 143 yards in 25 carries, and scored 
on a 10-yard run in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Estancia took a 7-0 lead in the third quarter. Quarterback Danny Ucker passed 
to Mike Aulet for 31 yards, and three plays later, Ucker scored on a seven-yard 
keeper with 4:25 left in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Gary Burrows ran for a 28-yard score on the next series. 
</P>
<P>
Estancia (5-0) has allowed only one touchdown this season, that coming in the 
second game of the season against Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
The Estancia defense was led by interceptions by Ty Hilbert and Oliver Wright, 
and sacks by Jeremie Chapin and Kevin Thomas. 
</P>
<P>
Orange, which had posted two shutouts of its own before Saturday night, fell to 
3-1-1 with the loss. STUART MATTHEWS 
</P>
</TEXT>
