<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOOD STUDENTS TO BE REWARDED WITH JACKETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Seniors with a cumulative grade point average of 3.5 or higher will be 
presented with Westchester High School academic jackets at a special ceremony 
sponsored by the Academic Booster Club at 7 p.m. Wednesday in the high school 
auditorium, 7400 W. Manchester Ave. 
</P>
<P>
The booster club launched the jacket program in 1984, only the third such 
program in the Los Angeles Unified School District. The organization is 
composed of representatives of local businesses and organizations, as well as 
parents and teachers. 
</P>
<P>
Edward (Chip) Anderson of the UCLA Graduate School of Education will be keynote 
speaker for the program. Also participating will be Eileen Banta, high school 
principal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
